<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>purissima</i> and/or <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>rudis</i> are dominant
or characteristically present in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>crustacea</i> ssp. <i>eastwoodiana</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>cuneatus</i> var. <i>fascicularis</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>impressus</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>aurantiacus</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>ericoides</i>, <i>Eriophyllum</i> <i>confertiflorum</i>, <i>Helianthemum</i> <i>scoparium</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i> and <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>parvula</i> var. <i>shrevei</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 5 m; canopy is open to continuous. Herbaceous layer is variable, and may include cryptogamic crust. </div>
</div>

        
