    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p>Stands are restricted to old stabilized dune sands of the Lompoc and Nipomo areas along the southern California Coast (261Ba-b) in northern Santa Barbara and in southern San Luis Obispo Cos. They contain distinctive aspects of the maritime chaparral (see maritime chaparral discussion in the Changes Since the First Edition section). Stands occur at Vandenberg Air Force Base, Burton Mesa, northeastern sections of the San Antonio Terrace, and other level areas such as the ridge top and foothills of the Purissima Hills (Meyer 2004, Holland and Keil 2007). At least five stands have been sampled in the Burton Mesa area with varying cover of the indicator manzanita species (Condor Environmental Services Inc. 2004).</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Southern California Coast</b> (261Ba-b). None</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
